      <p class="step-label">Step 9 of 9</p>
      <h1>Prepare for Your First Competition</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Final preparations and competition day essentials.</p>
      <section class="content-section">
        <p>Before the first event, make sure the robot, drive team, paperwork, and travel plan are all ready. The goal is not perfection, but arriving organized and able to compete safely.</p>
        <div class="content-subsection">
          <h3>Competition checklist</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Robot is tested and packed with chargers, batteries, and backup parts</li>
            <li>Driver, coach, and pit roles are assigned clearly</li>
            <li>Notebook, registration materials, and event schedule are ready</li>
            <li>Snacks, water, tools, and a repair kit are packed for the day</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <p><strong>Action:</strong> Do a full practice run before event day so the team can catch missing items early.</p>
      </section>
